    "description": "The purpose of this strategy is to outperform SPY across most market conditions by trading SPY as a single-asset directional system that selectively reduces or reverses exposure only when downside risk becomes statistically significant. The algorithm maintains a rolling history of daily SPY returns and applies wavelet-based denoising to extract the underlying structure of the return series. A support-vector regression model is then used to estimate the next-period return, which is normalized by recent realized volatility to form a dimensionless “edge” metric. This framework keeps the strategy long SPY by default, reflecting the market’s long-term positive drift, but temporarily shifts to a short position when the normalized edge becomes sufficiently negative and broader trend conditions confirm a risk-off regime. By acting only on large, volatility-adjusted deviations rather than continuous signals, the approach seeks to capture equity upside while avoiding prolonged drawdowns during adverse market environments.",
